"title": "1444: revelation, in NT",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1444: revelation, in nt",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The NT fulfils and completes the revelation of God which began in the OT. Jesus Christ is the central focus of this self-revelation of God.</p>\n<h2>The unity and progress of revelation</h2>\n<h3>The unity of OT and NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:17-Matt5:18\">MAT 5:17–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:21-Rom3:22\">ROM 3:21–3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:14-2Tim3:15\">2TI 3:14–3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:15-2Pet3:16\">2PE 3:15–3:16</a> <em>The writings of Paul are presented as having equal status with the OT Scriptures</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:18-Rev22:19\">REV 22:18–22:19</a> <em>These sanctions have the same force as those of <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:2\">Dt 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:32\">12:32</a>.</em></p>\n<h3>The progress of NT revelation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:1-Heb1:2\">HEB 1:1–1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:1-Heb2:4\">HEB 2:1–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:22-Heb12:27\">HEB 12:22–12:27</a></p>\n<h2>The NT fulfils and completes God's revelation of himself</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the supreme revelation of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:25-Col1:27\">COL 1:25–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:9-John1:18\">JHN 1:9–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:6\">JHN 14:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:12\">ACT 4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4\">GAL 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6-Phil2:8\">PHP 2:6–2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the image of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">2CO 4:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15\">COL 1:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ has the nature of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:6\">PHP 2:6</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the exact representation of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is the incarnate Word of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The role of the Holy Spirit in revelation</h2>\n<h3>He is the divine agent of revelation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:12-John16:15\">JHN 16:12–16:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16-John14:17\">JHN 14:16–14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:6\">1JN 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:6\">1JN 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:7\">REV 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:11\">REV 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:17\">REV 2:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:29\">REV 2:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:6\">REV 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:13\">REV 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:22\">REV 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>He is the source of revelatory manifestations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:7–12:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:1-Acts2:12\">ACT 2:1–2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6\">ROM 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28-1Cor12:30\">1CO 12:28–12:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:8-1Cor13:12\">1CO 13:8–13:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1-1Cor14:33\">1CO 14:1–14:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's purposes in revelation</h2>\n<h3>To reveal himself in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:15-Col1:20\">COL 1:15–1:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:44-John12:45\">JHN 12:44–12:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:4\">2CO 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>To reveal his plan through Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:25-Rom16:27\">ROM 16:25–16:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:7-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:7–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:3-Eph3:11\">EPH 3:3–3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:20\">COL 1:19–1:20</a></p>",
